New Records: Walker Kessler recorded 18 points, 14 rebounds, and five blocks against the Nuggets, which is the fourth time in his career that he has scored at least 15 points, grabbed at least 10 rebounds, and blocked at least five shots.
Key Match Events: Nikola Jokic nearly recorded a triple-double with 27 points, 16 rebounds, and nine assists.
Keyonte George had a 16-point, eight-assist, two-turnover night against the Nuggets.
Pre-Game Insights: There are no pre-game insights in this article.
Post-Match Reflections: The Jazz will celebrate any positives they can, and so far this season, the center's development has been a much-needed victory.
The Jazz will travel to face the Chicago Bulls at 6:30 p.m. MST on Monday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Walker Kessler is averaging career highs with 9.6 points, 11.1 rebounds, and 3.0 blocks while shooting a personal-best 63 percent from the free-throw line.
Keyonte George is shooting 12-22 on twos over his last four games, good for 54 percent inside the arc.
Others: The Jazz are 0-6 to start the season.
The Jazz will be televised on KJZZ, streamed on Jazz+, and heard on 97.5 The KSL Sports Zone.
